-- FACTBOX: Sovereign funds M&A deals surge in 2008
-- 
-- Thu Sep 4, 2008 5:02am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/04/us-sovereign-funds-factbox-idUSSIN6478920080904

 

 SINGAPORE  (Reuters) - Sovereign funds have invested $25.5 billion so far this year to acquire stakes in global companies such as Citigroup ( C.N ) and Merrill Lynch MER.N, up 66 percent from a year earlier, Thomson Reuters data showed on Thursday. 

 Following is a table that shows target nations, deals involving Singapore sovereign funds and total deals (completed and announced deals). M&A Deals involving sovereign wealth funds: Date Value ($billion) Deals Jan 1 to Aug 28, 2008 $25.487 22 Jan 1 to Aug 28, 2007 $15.401 28 Deals by the Govt of Singapore Investment Corp and Temasek Date Value ($billion) Deals Jan 1 to Aug 28, 2008 $9.1 10 Jan 1 to Aug 28, 2007 $6.2 17 Top three M&A markets for SWFs Target Nation ($billion) Market Number share of deals United States $15.8 62 pct 8 Russian Federation $5.3 21 pct 1 Singapore $1.3 5 pct 3 (To read a story on sovereign wealth funds' globalbuying spree, click on <ID:nSIN171848>) (Reporting by Saeed Azhar; Editing by Kim Coghill)